        "scopecontent": [
            {
                "id": "aspace_0772c8e8f3e2a8ea813fc33b4183bd69",
                "head": {
                    "value": "Scope and Content Note"
                },
                "p": [
                    {
                        "value": "\u003cspan class=\"ead-emph ead-emph-bold\"\u003eSeries I\u003c/span\u003e, consists of a typed copy of a letter from Amery to Lincoln Brigade archivist Victor Berch recounting experiences of the MacKenzie-Papineau Battalion. \u003cspan class=\"ead-emph ead-emph-bold\"\u003eSeries II\u003c/span\u003e, consists of two autobiographical typescripts: \"The Worm Turns,\" and \"Something More.\" The reminiscences are extremely frank in their details of Amery's personal life."
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
